<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-02T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-02T15:00:00-05:00" n="763" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d763">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6614: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gade</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-02T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">April 2,
                                            1920—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Supplementing Department’s March 31, 5 p.m.</p>
                            <p>If your investigation confirms report that Esthonia is planning to
                                deliver officers of Northwestern Russian Army to the Bolsheviki,
                                Department feels that food supplies should be withheld until
                                guarantee is received from Esthonia that it will not turn these men
                                over to Soviet Government.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>